node.text:
Bonnie was invited on stage at the Orlando Advanced Week Long Retreat to share her story of healing from Guillain-Barre Syndrome, a rare autoimmune condition that can lead to complete paralysis. Her diagnosis was later changed to Chronic Inflammatory Demyelinating Polyneuropathy, with a similar dire prognosis. Bonnie was a Give to Give Foundation scholarship recipient. For more information about Give to Give:
https://givetogivefoundation.org

From Bonnie (posted on Facebook 5/25/21):
I can honestly say that one of the greatest highlights of my life was getting up on this stage in front of 1,350 people and sharing my story about how I healed myself from a chronic autoimmune disease, CIDP.
I was originally diagnosed w/ GBS and then it was changed to Chronic Inflammatory Demyelinating Polyneuropathy. I lost the feeling of and ability to move or use my feet and legs.
I was told that I could be dependent on a walker or wheelchair for the rest of my life and that I would need either the treatments such as plasma exchange or IV treatments or steroids or other medications (all w/ harmful side effects) for the rest of my life.
I was introduced to the work of Dr Joe Dispenza and I immersed myself into his work and this is what I attribute my healing to. Our mind and the thoughts we tell ourselves and the resulting emotions that those thoughts create is what determines our reality.
I am here as an example as proof that we were born to be creators, not simply victims to our circumstances. I knew this terrifying experience was happening for me to teach me the lessons I needed to know in order to become my future self, the person who I am destined to be.  I will gladly help anyone who would like to know more.  Here is a snippet of my experience.

Recorded in April 2021.

node.text:
Dr Joe on whether we could live to 150 years old; a clip from our May Dr Joe Live conversation.

Have you ever wanted to ask Dr Joe a question about the Work? You could have the opportunity to do so during our Dr Joe Live. Every month, Dr Joe carves out an hour to connect with his community to answer questions about the application of this work. These subscription-based conversations are for anybody who is interested in transforming their life.

Click the link in bio to learn more & register to join Dr Joe and the rest of the community for this month’s class, which will be on Thursday June 24th 12:00pm (PST) // 3:00PM (EST) on Zoom. Register early so as to receive your Zoom link in time.
 
While these conversations are live, the two most recent episodes can also be accessed later in the subscriber’s online library.

When you join Dr Joe Live, you’ll also be the first to know about our upcoming planned Live Events before they are posted on our website as we announce at the end of each class. 

Dr Joe Live is available in English, Spanish, German & French.

Suzanne, a massage therapist, shared Dr Joe's “Blessing of the Energy Centers” meditation with a client who had just been diagnosed with cancer (metastasized melanoma throughout his body). She integrated the meditation into her treatments, and he eventually was also practicing the meditation at home several days a week. His medical team also administered 4 treatments of immunotherapy medication. Suzanne shared his most recent PET scan from April 2021....wow! 

Recorded at the Orlando Advanced Week Long Retreat in April 2021.

node.text:
When we get beyond our associations to everything known in the material world and enter—as an awareness—the non-material, non-physical unifying quantum field, there is an entirely different set of rules than those in 3-dimensional reality. In the field, there is no space and time as we know it, and because there is no space and no time, there is no separation. Therefore, if there is no separation, we are connected to everything.

When we enter the field of infinite frequencies as pure consciousness, every thought we have in this realm produces an energy or frequency. Since every new creation starts with a thought, all we have to do to create something new is become conscious –as an awareness–  of a new thought that will create a new experience in the material world. If we can feel the frequency of that thought and stay aware of it—stay connected to it, notice it, pay attention to it, be present with it, and entrain our energy to it (that is to say, if we can become more of it and less of us)—now we're connected to the energy of that potential reality. Since the field creates matter, when we create from the field instead of matter to matter, we can exert greater, more immediate effects in our material world.

Our Synchronizing Your Energy Meditation Series is a great tool for this. Click the link in our bio to learn more.

node.text:
Most people create from polarity. Polarity - or duality -  means ‘I don’t have what I want, and because I don’t have what I want, I want to get what I don’t have.’ This is the state from which most people try to get what they want - a state of lack. There is nothing wrong with this process; it’s how we evolve who we are. However, it will always take time for us to reach our goals and realize our dreams by this mode of creation.

The reason is this: When we create from lack, we are using our senses to define reality. We are matter creating matter, limited by the laws of time and space.  Therefore, it takes time to get what we want and we are enslaved to the laws of 3-dimensional reality.

But if we are creating from a state of abundance, wholeness, or worthiness, we’re no longer looking for anything. We are creating from a place of already having it. That’s the moment we’re out of the way and we begin to draw experiences, opportunities, and new events to us.

What are you creating at this moment? Comment below.

node.text:
Think about the last time you fell in love with someone or the person with whom you are in love. How does it feel? First off, it’s exciting. The thought of seeing them, spending time, sharing experiences, and communing with them is inspiring. When you do get to spend time with them, you feel connected, expanded, locked in, and aware of the moment you’re sharing. You listen, you’re patient, and you’re present. You give of your heart, your time, and your gifts, and in turn, you receive the same. In a healthy relationship, each person feels worthy of the other, and each person matches the efforts of the other—not because they have to, but because they want to.  In that union is a feeling of wholeness and completeness, and in the union where two become one is found profound truths and experiences greater than the self.

The same is true of our relationship with the divine. The idea of going into your meditation with the excitement and energy of seeing someone you love—with the excitement of having a love affair—is the exact energy that makes you connect with it. It’s this level of excitement and enthusiasm that draws it closer to you…because it is love—and just like a relationship, the more you love, the bigger your love gets. It is love that bonds us together.

node.text:
People who stop and transmute fear into an elevated emotion, despite anxiety and the body’s resistance, will tell you that they too were afraid to step into the unknown, but their passion for their vision was greater than their fear. They will also tell you that the effort was worth the reward of what they found on the other side—liberation, freedom, wholeness, and more self-love.

It makes sense that the emotions of your future dreams should be the emotions you’re living by when you are conscious in your everyday life, because the moment you disconnect from these emotions you’re back to feeling lack and separation from your future. But if you’re staying in that elevated emotional state of the future throughout your day, and your passion for your vision is greater than your fear of the unknown or fear of failure, then your body feels like that future event has already happened. This is how we transcend the emotion of fear, one day at a time. That’s a new state of being with a new energy—a new personality creating a new personal reality.

When we feel as though what we’re creating has already happened, we’re less likely to judge ourselves, and analyze or overthink why our future hasn’t yet happened. In fact, if we feel that our future has already happened, we will be less likely to try to force, predict, fight for, or control outcomes in our life. Why would we do that if we conditioned our body into feeling as though our new future has already happened?

If you truly and repeatedly conditioned your body to feel thankful, appreciative, empowered, free, and in love with life every day, it makes sense that in time, you would trust your future completely. 
It’s also likely that stepping into and trusting the unknown will create new opportunities that you would have never seen coming—until you stepped out of your predictable life and into your unknown future.

node.text:
If we can feel this way after the fact, there’s no reason it can’t happen beforehand.
How do we tap into this energy and use it to create change? First, start with a clear intention. Maybe you’d like to get a new job that pays better and gives you more control over your time. Create that inner world, fill it with rich detail. You’ll want to be specific about what you want because this helps create the necessary elevated emotion. 

Next, ask yourself how you would feel if you got what you wanted. Referring back to our example, how would you feel if you got that new job? A good way to think of this concept is by switching the question around to ask why you are looking for a new job in the first place. The answers here could be anything from respect to financial security. This is the feeling you want to focus on and manifest in your brain and body. The combination of creating a clear intention and harnessing a sponsoring emotion results in a new state of being.

The next step is to mentally rehearse the choices you will make, what things you will do, what experiences await you and how you will feel. If clear intention focuses on the “what” then this step focuses on the “how” you will go about creating the change necessary to get that new job.

Soon, your body and mind will respond as if the event or experience has already happened. You’ll be flooded with the same chemicals that are normally released when you feel grateful only this time you’re drawing the possibility to you. You know you are doing it properly when ‘you feel like the event has already happened’—that’s gratitude.

node.text:
I often say that this is a time in history when it’s not enough to just know, but to know how.

Whether we are advancing the understanding of the quantum model of reality, reviewing how to create from the field instead of from matter, or deconstructing and reconstructing the breath so as to move energy from the body into the brain, in this work, we want to help our students understand what they are doing in the most methodical way possible. In reviewing all of these different elements and aspects of “the formula”—including opening our hearts, the role of electromagnetism, altering our brainwave states, and how this can influence epigenetics, our personality, and ultimately our personal reality—we can then jump right into our meditations while the information is fresh.

In combining knowledge, information, and theory, we prepare our students for the experience. By understanding what they are doing from a greater level of mind, many are able to reignite their passion, so they feel more empowered, more inspired, and better able to understand what’s possible. I really want to make this work so full of information and intense practice that when it comes time for our students to do their daily meditations without me, they are re-empowered into a greater level of transformation.

Bonnie was invited on stage at the Orlando Advanced Week Long Retreat to share her story of healing from Guillain-Barre Syndrome, a rare autoimmune condition that can lead to complete paralysis. Her diagnosis was later changed to Chronic Inflammatory Demyelinating Polyneuropathy, with a similar dire prognosis. Bonnie was a Give to Give Foundation scholarship recipient. For more information about Give to Give:
https://givetogivefoundation.org

From Bonnie (posted on Facebook 5/25/21):
I can honestly say that one of the greatest highlights of my life was getting up on this stage in front of 1,350 people and sharing my story about how I healed myself from a chronic autoimmune disease, CIDP.
I was originally diagnosed w/ GBS and then it was changed to Chronic Inflammatory Demyelinating Polyneuropathy. I lost the feeling of and ability to move or use my feet and legs.
I was told that I could be dependent on a walker or wheelchair for the rest of my life and that I would need either the treatments such as plasma exchange or IV treatments or steroids or other medications (all w/ harmful side effects) for the rest of my life.
I was introduced to the work of Dr Joe Dispenza and I immersed myself into his work and this is what I attribute my healing to. Our mind and the thoughts we tell ourselves and the resulting emotions that those thoughts create is what determines our reality.
I am here as an example as proof that we were born to be creators, not simply victims to our circumstances. I knew this terrifying experience was happening for me to teach me the lessons I needed to know in order to become my future self, the person who I am destined to be.  I will gladly help anyone who would like to know more.  Here is a snippet of my experience.

Recorded in April 2021.

node.text:
The commonalties these traits share are that they all involve reaching out to others, which in turn takes attention off ourselves.

Putting all of our attention on ourselves is normal when we are living in stress, survival, fear, anger, competition, frustration, resentment, pain, suffering, or anxiety. Obviously, in survival we need to take care of our body, pay attention to the environment, and think about time. In these situations, it’s all about putting the self first. The thing is that, in our current culture, the majority of our threats are not life-threatening, but rather, they are an assault on our mental, psychological, and emotional well-being. All of this is to say that we have to lay down the very thing that keeps us creating the same life in order to create a new reality.

As the new sciences tell us, it’s not about survival of the fittest, but survival of the community. One of the key elements, then, becomes the concept of emergence. Like a group of fish all swimming together in unison as one mind, or a huge population of birds flying in a beautiful array of changing patterns and formations, the collective behavior of a community is qualitatively different than the behaviors of the individuals. Thus, the collective community of individuals synchronized as one gives an appearance of a larger organism. How are you connecting with your community? Comment below.
